Suppose it is true, that the negro is inferior to the white, in the gifts of nature;
               is it not the exact reverse justice that the white should, forthis^that^reason, take from the negro, any part of the little which has been given him? "Giveto him that is needy" is the christian rule of charity; but "Take from him that is
               needy" is the rule of slavery–
